\f0\b \cf0 1. "Bringing in the Light"
\f1\b0 \cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 1. Close your eyes. Take a deep breath. \
\
2. Visualize a brilliant, golden-white column of light descending from the cosmos, from the heart of God. \
\
3. See this light entering the top of your head, your crown chakra. \
\
4. Feel it cascading down, filling your entire body\'97your head, your throat, your heart, your solar plexus, every organ, every cell. \
\
5. As it fills you, it pushes out all that is not light: all density, fear, sadness. \
\
6. Sit in this pillar of light for 1-5 minutes, breathing deeply.\cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Offered as a foundational daily practice for energetic hygiene, clearing, and protection. Used to begin meditations or to clear energy after a difficult interaction.\cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 "Do not 
\f3\i try
\f1\i0  too hard. It is not an effort. It is an allowing, a receiving."\cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

