\f0\b \cf0 2. "Transmuting Energy with the Breath"
\f1\b0 \cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 1. Identify the energy you wish to transmute (e.g., anxiety, anger). \
\
2. Locate where it lives in your body (e.g., a tightness in the chest, a knot in the stomach). \
\
3. Breathe 
\f3\i into
\f1\i0  that location. On the inhale, consciously breathe light and love 
\f3\i into
\f1\i0  the dense energy. \
\
4. On the exhale, consciously release the transformed, lighter energy back to the universe. \
\
5. Repeat 10 times, intending for the energy to be dissolved and transmuted by your love.\cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 Taught as an "in the moment" tool for emotional alchemy, to be used when triggered.\cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0
\cf0 "Do not judge the energy. Do not make it wrong. Simply be the alchemist. Be the love that transforms it."\cell 
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

